The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, April 9: A 10-year-old boy and a woman were killed this evening after a gas cyl-inder exploded in their house in Metiabruz. 

 Police said Reshma Bano, 30, and Ali Khan died on the spot. Four other members of their family have been hospitalised. Reshma was cooking along with her younger sister when the cylinder burst, a police officer said.

 Calcutta: Two schoolmates were found frothing from their mouths on a field in Sonarpur on Sunday morning. An empty bottle was lying beside them. Residents rushed them to a nursing home, where Debashish Mondal, 14, was de- clared dead and Rathin Mondal, 15, is battling for life. Police said they were Class IX students of the same school. 

 Durgapur: Joydeep Mukherjee, 52, a doctor at Durgapur Projects Ltd Hospital, committed suicide on Sunday by injecting an overdose of anaesthesia. Police said a dispute in the family had left him depressed.




